
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>BookTracker</title>
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.8/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" integrity="sha384-sRIl4kxILFvY47J16cr9ZwB07vP4J8+LH7qKQnuqkuIAvNWLzeN8tE5YBujZqJLB" crossorigin="anonymous">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="./styles/main.css">
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Domine:wght@400..700&family=Libre+Baskerville:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&family=Roboto:ital,wght@0,100..900;1,100..900&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
   
</head>
<body>
<section class="container, intro">
    <div class="container">
        <h1>BARILON BOOKS SERIES</h1>
        <h2>Books I have read</h2>
        <p>
         My Book Tracker helps you organize your reading journey. Search for <span>books</span>, view their <span>covers </span>and <span>authors</span>, record your <span>dates</span>, <span>ratings</span>, and <span>reflections</span> — all in one place. It’s a simple way to remember what you’ve read and how each book inspired you.
        </p>
        <hr>
    </div>
</section>
<section class="container-fluid">
  <div class="container content">
    <% if (locals.books && books.length > 0) { %>
      <% books.forEach(function(book) { %>
        <div class="book-item">
          <img 
            src=<%= book.cover_url %>
            alt="Book Cover" 
            class="book-cover"
          >
          <div class="book-info">
            <h2 class="book-title">
              "<%= book.book_title %>" by <%= book.author %>
            </h2>
            <p>
              <strong>Date Read:</strong> <%= book.date_read %><br>
              <strong>Rating:</strong> <%= book.rating %>/10
            </p>
            <p class="book-summary">
              <%= book.summary %>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      <% }) %>

    <% } else { %>
      <div class="book-item">
        <img 
          src="https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/6632621-M.jpg" 
          alt="Book Cover" 
          class="book-cover"
        >
        <div class="book-info">
          <h2 class="book-title">
            "The Alchemist" by Paulo Coelho
          </h2>
          <p>
            <strong>Date Read:</strong> March 15, 2023<br>
            <strong>Rating:</strong> 5/5
          </p>
          <p class="book-summary">
            "The Alchemist" is a novel by Paulo Coelho that tells the story of Santiago, 
            a young shepherd from Spain who dreams of finding a hidden treasure located 
            near the Egyptian pyramids. Encouraged by a mysterious king, Santiago embarks 
            on a journey across the desert, encountering various characters who teach him 
            valuable life lessons. The novel explores themes of destiny, personal legend, 
            and the importance of following one's dreams. Through his adventures, Santiago 
            learns to listen to his heart and discovers that the true treasure lies not in 
            material wealth but in self-discovery and spiritual fulfillment.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    <% } %>

  </div>
</section>

<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.8/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js" integrity="sha384-FKyoEForCGlyvwx9Hj09JcYn3nv7wiPVlz7YYwJrWVcXK/BmnVDxM+D2scQbITxI" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
</body>
</html>